# Per-client token registry for the Chrome native bridge.
#
# This file is OPTIONAL and ADDITIVE to bridge_token.txt. The single token in
# bridge_token.txt is always registered as the `default` client; any named
# clients defined here are added on top of it.
#
# Format: one client per line, `name:token` (split on the first ':'). Both the
# name and token are stripped of surrounding whitespace. Blank lines and lines
# beginning with '#' are ignored.
#
# Copy this file to `bridge_tokens.txt` (same directory) or point
# BRIDGE_TOKENS_FILE at your own path, then add real clients below.
#
# Examples (commented out):
# alice:3f9c1d7a2b8e4f06a1c5d9e8b7f60213
# ci-runner:9a2b4c6d8e0f1a3b5c7d9e1f2a4b6c8d
